entries.name: TokenBridge
entries.description: Contract used to bridge and escrow ERC-20 tokens.

entries.name: L2Roles
entries.description: The Zodiac 'Roles' module for Safe multisigs allows defining roles that can call preconfigured targets on behalf of the Gnosis Safe.

receivedPermissions.description: can pause the L2MessageService, the TokenBridge and the L2USDCBridge.
can mint XP soulbound tokens as part of the Voyage campaign.

entries.name: L2USDCBridge
entries.description: L2 side of the old and now unused USDC bridge.

receivedPermissions.description: can prevent tokens that have not been bridged already from being bridged by assigning them a reserved status.
can remove the reserved status from a token, meaning that it is allowed to be bridged again.
can set custom ERC20 contracts for specific ERC20s.
propose transactions.

entries.name: L2Timelock
entries.description: A standard timelock with access control. The current minimum delay is 0s.

directlyReceivedPermissions.description: manage all access control roles and change the minimum delay.

entries.name: LineaVoyageXP
entries.description: Voyage XP tokens are non-transferrable, soulbound tokens that are distributed to recognize the community’s contribution toward the growth of the Linea ecosystem.

entries.name: BridgedToken
entries.description: Standard implementation used for assets that are native to the other layer and are bridged to this layer.

entries.name: UpgradeableBeacon
entries.description: A beacon with an upgradeable implementation currently set as linea:0xda8AEFCf0F9B0b81915a2C124f913e58212D49dF. Beacon proxy contracts pointing to this beacon will all use its implementation.

receivedPermissions.description: can pause the bridge.
can pause the bridge.
can pause token bridging actions initiated from the other layer.
can pause token bridging actions initiated from this layer.
can prevent tokens that have not been bridged already from being bridged by assigning them a reserved status.
can remove the reserved status from a token, meaning that it is allowed to be bridged again.
can set custom ERC20 contracts for specific ERC20s.
can set the contract that is recognized to be the token bridge contract on the other side.
can set the contract used as the source of truth from crosschain messages.
can unpause token bridging actions initiated from the other layer.
can unpause token bridging actions initiated from this layer.
manage all critical access control roles and permissions (full admin of the main bridge escrow).
cancel queued transactions.
execute transactions that are ready.
manage all access control roles and change the minimum delay.
propose transactions.
change the beacon implementation.
